text:
News Syria's war: Suicide attacks hit miltary in Homs War monitor says at least 10 people killed following attacks on state facilities in the country's third-largest city. 25 Feb 2017 07:41 GMT 
Twin suicide attacks on military installations in Syria's government-held city of Homs have killed at least 10 people. 
The UK-based Syrian Observatory for Human Rights said on Saturday that loud explosions and gunfire were heard following the assault in the western city. 
"The attacks hit the headquarters of state security and military intelligence in two central districts," Syrian Observatory director Rami Abdel Rahman told AFP news agency. 
It was unclear what group the assailants belonged to. 
The attacks come as peace negotiators continue talks for the second day in Geneva over Syria's six-year-old civil war that has killed hundreds of thousands of people.
